What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Tunable Filter Market?

Market Analysis and Insights

Tunable Filter Market

Tunable filter market is expected to gain market growth in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research analyses the tunable filter market to exhibit a CAGR of 6.8% for the forecast period of 2021-2028 and will reach USD 238.9 million by 2028.

Tunable filter is an analog device that allows the passing of the narrow bandwidth of light and blocking all the others, and it operates on the principle of polarization dispersion which helps in the spectral analysis. It consists of electrical filters in which the frequency of the rejection band or passband can be varied by adjusting the components.

The increasing adoption of liquid crystal tunable filters for electronic imaging application across the globe will emerge as the major factor driving market growth. The increase in the demand for these microscopes along with developments in the field of science and technology along with growing utilization of the acoustic-optic tunable filters owing to its reliable and stable tuning of the wavelength will further aggravate the market value. However, high cost of tunable filters associated with the research activities and development act as a restraint for the market.

In addition to this, rising technological advancements demand LCFTs for a wide array of applications across different systems, create new opportunities for growing the market within the forecast period. The presence of low-quality tunable filters in the market and concerns regarding the poor spectral performance of the tunable filter will dampen the growth rate that further result as a challenge for the market.

